node.text:
Video tour of The Syshaus designed by @studio.arthurcasas.

The Syshaus is the future of housing. It is a concept with constructive system with a standardized 1.2m grid system that allows the house to be built within 6 months. The keywords are quality, practicality, and sustainability, and eliminates the hassle of constructing a house.

Host: @christiantrampe

node.text:
Describe this home in ONE word! 😍
The Amchit Residence is a modern beach house open towards the sea with expansive sun decks and shielded from the road. The home is designed by @blankpagearchitects + @karimnaderstudio and is located in Amchitt, Lebanon // Photos by @ieva.saudargaite.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

node.text:
Who’d love this backyard? 😍
The Dave Blanchard House is a contemporary home taking inspiration from the traditional gable house. The floating lounging creates an interesting design element, which also ensures that lots of time will be spent outdoors. The house is designed by Bindon Design Group and is located in Auckland, New Zealand // Photos by @duncaninnesphotography.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
Swipe left! Dope or nope? 😍
Àtic Blanc is – as its name suggests – a white penthouse in the center of the Spanish city Valencia, seeking to reinterpret this specific type of housing. The home is accessed in the center, separating the day area and the night area with terraces favoring natural cross ventilation. It is designed by @fransilvestrearquitectos who have long been known for their consistency in terms of extreme minimalism. // Photos by @diegoopazo.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
How cool is this? 😍
Villa Seascape is a contemporary, tropical residence with a beach-chic colour scheme. Accessed from the aerial walkway above the living area is a netting-floored mezzanine suspended like a huge hammock above the guest kitchen; perfect for kids or adventurous souls. The house is located in Nusa Lembongan, Bali, Indonesia // Video by @rizromauli.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
Swipe left! What do you think?
The X6, Two in One House is a dual home balancing touches of concrete, wood, black and white. From the outside, the house looks like a singular home, but the inside tells a different story: Two brothers, two separate programs and two houses placed harmoniously side by side, with a common wall separating them. The house is designed by @razmel.architect and is located in Tel Aviv // Photos by @itaybenitphotographer.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

Swipe left! What do you think? 😍
The Metrick Cottage is a one-story residence and boathouse on the shore of Lake Joseph, Ontario. Settled in a rocky enclave of waterfront homes, this year-round retreat draws inspiration from the surrounding natural beauty creating a warm, elegant and eco-friendly home. The house is designed by @akbarchitects. // Photos by @shaigilfoto.

node.text:
How cool is this? 😍
CP1R is an architectural concept attempting to challenge the norms of conventional design. Imprinted to a cliffside, the concept takes advantage of the natural cliff’s hues and textures that add a unique character to the modern industrial kitchen. The concept is designed and visualized by @igor_sirotov_architects from Ukraine.

node.text:
Thoughts on this entrance? 🤔
The Natal House is a residential project on a site with a 4.5 m incline. While this incline seems to be a challenge at first, it enhances the architectural expression as the entrance pathway beautifully winds its way to the front door. The house is designed by @camillasoares and will be built in Natal, Brazil // Visuals by @pixelapixel.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

node.text:
In the historic and cultural ancient capital, Kyoto, Aman’s secluded 80-acre property creates a respite in the heart of one of Japan's most visited cities. With a blend of authentic, traditional ryokan hospitality and contemporary spaces, each room captures a contemporary, minimalistic style with a nod to the quintessential ryokan feel; walls of windows bringing the outside in to spacious, light-filled interiors. @aman_kyoto is designed by Kerry Hill Architects // Photos by @benrich__.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!
